23/01/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- A parliamentary panel reviewed 12 of the 45 articles in a draft law regulating the future functioning of the judiciary Tuesday (January 22nd). 
Deputy commission chief Fatmir Xhafaj, of the opposition Socialist Party, said after the meeting that the commission has heard from experts and has agreed on most articles in the bill. 
Debate on the remaining issues will continue. 
(Koha Jona, Shekulli, Korrieri, GazetaShqip - 23/01/08; Balkanweb, To-Channel - 22/01/08)
